The paper deals with problems related to matrix and tensor rank, which are fundamental concepts in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves linear algebraic techniques and optimization methods, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.NA (numerical analysis). Finally, the paper may have applications in signal processing (cs.SI), which involves the analysis and manipulation of multidimensional data structures such as tensors.
